text: Trochaclis is a genus of sea snails, marine gastropod mollusks in the family Ataphridae. ==Species== Species within the genus Trochaclis include: * Trochaclis antarctica Thiele, 1912 * Trochaclis attenuata Marshall, 1995 * Trochaclis calva Marshall, 1995 * Trochaclis cristata Marshall, 1995 * Trochaclis elata Marshall, 1995 * Trochaclis islandica Warén, 1989 * Trochaclis regalis Marshall, 1995 * Trochaclis versiliensis Warén, Carrozza & Rocchini in Warén, 1992 ==References== * Gofas, S.; Le Renard, J.; Bouchet, P. (2001). Mollusca, in: Costello, M.J. et al. (Ed.) (2001). European register of marine species: a check-list of the marine species in Europe and a bibliography of guides to their identification. Collection Patrimoines Naturels, 50: pp. 180–213 * Marshall, B.A. 1995: Recent and Tertiary Trochaclididae from the southwest Pacific (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Trochoidae). The Veliger 38: 92-115. Category:Ataphridae
title: Trochaclis
